Performance in a Hosted Stand-Up/Sketch Comedy Program or Series\n|[[Gemini Awards]]\n|Best Performance in a Hosted Stand-Up/Sketch Comedy Program or Series\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[30 Rock]]''\n|[[Writers Guild of America Award]]\n|[[Writers Guild of America]]\n|Outstanding Achievement \u2013 Comedy Series\n|{{nom}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.wga.org/content/default.aspx?id=4779|accessdate=November 16, 2014|title=2012 Writers Guild Awards Television, News, Radio, Promotional Writing, and Graphic Animation Nominees Announced|date=December 7, 2011|author=[[Writers Guild of America]]|work=[[Writers Guild of America Awards 2012]]|publisher=Wga.org|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714165809/http://www.wga.org/content/default.aspx?id=4779|archivedate=July 14, 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n|2012\n|[[Stand-up comedy|Stand-up routine]]\n|[[American Comedy Awards|American Comedy Award]]\n|[[Comedy Central]]\n|Best Club Comic\n|{{won}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://content.usatoday.com/communities/popcandy/post/2012/05/are-you-a-hannibal-buress-fan-yet/1#.VG2JhPnF_iU|accessdate=November 20, 2014|work=[[USA Today]]|title=Are you a Hannibal Buress fan yet?|date=May 9, 2012|archivedate=June 26, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120626135757/http://content.usatoday.com/communities/popcandy/post/2012/05/are-you-a-hannibal-buress-fan-yet/1|first=Whitney|last=Matheson}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|accessdate=November 20, 2014|title=Talking with Hannibal Buress About His Hour Special, 'The Eric Andre Show', and Enjoying the Moment|first=Jesse David|last=Fox|date=May 17, 2012|work=Splitsider|archivedate=January 27, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130127132911/http://splitsider.com/2012/05/talking-with-hannibal-buress-about-his-hour-special-the-eric-andre-show-enjoying-the-moment/|url=http://splitsider.com/2012/05/talking-with-hannibal-buress-about-his-hour-special-the-eric-andre-show-enjoying-the-moment/}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.carolines.com/comedian/hannibal-buress/|accessdate=November 20, 2014|title=Hannibal Buress|work=Carolines on Broadway|date=2014|archivedate=December 20, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131220172925/http://www.carolines.com/comedian/hannibal-buress/}}</ref>\n|-\n|2014\n|The Eric Andre Show\n|Best Talk Show Host\n|Adult Swim\n|Best Talk Show Host\n|{{Won}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n* {{official website|http://hannibalburess.com/}}\n* {{IMDb name|2868110}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Buress, Hannibal}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:African-American atheists]]\n[[Category:African Americans in the media]]\n[[Category:African-American male actors]]\n[[Category:African-American male comedians]]\n[[Category:African-American screenwriters]]\n[[Category:African-American stand-up comedians]]\n[[Category:American atheists]]\n[[Category:American male comedians]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:American television writers]]\n[[Category:American men podcasters]]\n[[Category:American podcasters]]\n[[Category:American stand-up comedians]]\n[[Category:Comedians from Illinois]]\n[[Category:Critics of religions]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Chicago]]\n[[Category:Male television writers]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from Illinois]]\n[[Category:Southern Illinois University Carbondale alumni]]\n[[Category:Writers from Chicago]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American comedian}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Hannibal Buress\n| image              = 7.29.12HannibalBuressByEzmosis.jpg\n| caption            = Buress in July 2012\n| birth_name         = Hannibal Amir Buress\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1983|2|4}}\n| birth_place        = [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], U.S.\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n*Comedian\n*actor\n*writer\n*producer\n}}\n| years_active       = 2002\u2013present\n| residence          = [[Wicker Park, Chicago|Wicker Park]], Illinois, U.S.\n| spouse             = \n| module             = {{Infobox comedian|embed=yes\n| medium       = {{flatlist|\n* Stand-up comedy\n* film\n* television\n}}\n| genre        = {{flatlist|\n* [[Observational comedy]]\n* [[black comedy]]\n* [[blue comedy]]\n* [[satire]]\n* [[surreal humour]]\n}}\n| subject      = {{flatlist|\n* African-American culture\n* American politics\n* current events\n* everyday life\n* human sexuality\n* popular culture\n* race relations\n* racism\n* food\n* religion\n* self-deprecation\n}}\n}}\n| website            = {{URL|http://hannibalburess.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Hannibal Amir Buress''' ({{IPAc-en|\u02c8|b|\u028cr|\u1d7b|s}}, born February 4, 1983) is an American comedian,<ref>{{cite web|work=[[NPR]]|title=Hannibal Buress and the Comedy of the Unexpected|author=NPR Staff|date=September 12, 2013|url=https://www.npr.org/2013/09/12/221456050/hannibal-buress-and-the-comedy-of-the-unexpected}}</ref> actor, writer, and producer. He started performing comedy in 2002 while attending Southern Illinois University.  He has co-starred on [[Adult Swim]]'s ''[[The Eric Andre Show]]'' since 2012 and was featured on Comedy Central's ''[[Broad City]]'' from 2014 to 2019.\n\n==Early life==\nHannibal Amir Buress<ref>{{Citation|last=BigBoyTV|title=Hannibal Buress on \"The Eric Andre Show\", Bill Cosby, And More! (Full Interview) {{!}} BigBoyTV|date=2016-08-30|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=707iciiRzDw|access-date=2018-06-25}}</ref> was born in [[Chicago, Illinois]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Fishman|first1=Elly|title=Is Hannibal Buress the Funniest Man Alive?|url=http://www.chicagomag.com/Chicago-Magazine/April-2014/Hannibal-Buress-Comedian/|website=Chicago Magazine|publisher=Chicago Tribune Media Group|accessdate=September 18, 2014}}</ref> on February 4, 1983,<ref>{{cite web|work=vita.mn|title=Interview: Hannibal Buress|author=Raghav Mehta|date=February 4, 2013|url= http://www.vita.mn/arts/246381811.html}}</ref> the son of teacher Margaret.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chicagomag.com/Chicago-Magazine/April-2014/Hannibal-Buress-Comedian/|title=Is Hannibal Buress the Funniest Man Alive?|work=Chicago magazine|access-date=2018-06-25|language=en}}</ref> Hannibal was quoted saying \"Get the fuck out my Dad's job\", possibly referring to his Mom's job too <ref>{{cite web |title=Hannibal Buress Goes Undercover on Twitter, YouTube and Wikipedia | GQ |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q_-IH2Y6o2Y |website=YouTube |accessdate=2020-04-15}}</ref>. He was raised in the [[Austin, Chicago|Austin]] neighborhood of Chicago. He was named after [[Ancient Carthage|Carthaginian]] General [[Hannibal|Hannibal Barca]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2011-06-15/entertainment/ct-ent-0616-hannibal-buress-20110615_1_hannibal-buress-zanies-executive-vice-president-rental-car|title=Comedian Hannibal Buress' star is rising|work=Chicago Tribune|accessdate=February 21, 2015}}</ref> and has told stories in his stand-up act about his name causing women to turn him down because of its association with fictional cannibal [[Hannibal Lecter]]. After attending [[Steinmetz College Prep]], he attended [[Southern Illinois University Carbondale]] for four years but did not graduate, where he became friends with hip hop artist [[Open Mike Eagle]], his [[resident adviser|RA]] at the time.<ref name=\"BA\">{{cite web|title=BA #064:'Open' Mike Eagle|url=http://boxangeles.com/2015/02/15/ba-064-open-mike-eagle/|website=Box Angeles podcast}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n[[File:Hannibal Buress (1808462347).jpg|thumb|Buress performing in October 2007]]\n[[File:Hannibal Hannibal Hannibal ... (4031486408).jpg|thumb|upright|right|Buress performing in October 2009]]\nBuress began his stand-up career at an open mic in 2002. He has been featured in ''The Awkward Comedy Show'' special on [[Comedy Central]], and alongside comics [[Baron Vaughn]], [[Eric Andre]], Marina Franklin, and [[Victor Varnado]], and on the [[FX (TV channel)|FX]] sitcom ''[[Louie (U.S. TV series)|Louie]]''. He currently co-stars as Eric Andre's sidekick on ''[[The Eric Andre Show]]'' on [[Adult Swim]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Evans|first=Bradford|title=Talking to Hannibal Buress About 'The Eric Andre Show', His Comedy Central Pilot, and 'Broad City'|url=http://splitsider.com/2013/10/talking-to-hannibal-buress-about-the-eric-andre-show-his-comedy-central-pilot-and-broad-city/|accessdate=October 29, 2013|newspaper=[[Splitsider]]|date=October 9, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014230049/http://splitsider.com/2013/10/talking-to-hannibal-buress-about-the-eric-andre-show-his-comedy-central-pilot-and-broad-city/|archive-date=October 14, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> In July 2010, Buress made [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] magazine's \"Ten Comics to Watch in 2010\" list.<ref>{{cite news|last=Heisler|first=Steve|title=10 Comics to Watch: Hannibal Buress|url=https://variety.com/2010/legit/news/10-comics-to-watch-hannibal-buress-1118021696/|accessdate=October 29, 2013|newspaper=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=July 13, 2010}}</ref>\n\nHis first stand-up comedy album ''My Name is Hannibal'' was released on July 27, 2010.\n\nBuress was a writer on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' from 2009 to 2010.<ref>{{cite news|work=[[The New York Times]]|title=Off-Kilter, Laid-Back Stand-Up|first=Jason|last=Zinoman|date=November 3, 2011|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/11/04/arts/hannibal-buress-approaches-comedy-from-the-side.html?_r=0}}</ref> He left having had only one of his sketches aired.<ref name=\"fishman2014\">{{cite web|last=Fishman|first=Elly|title=Is Hannibal Buress the Funniest Man Alive?|url=http://www.chicagomag.com/Chicago-Magazine/April-2014/Hannibal-Buress-Comedian/|publisher=Chicago magazine|year=2014}}</ref> In September 2010, he began writing for the fifth season of the [[NBC]] comedy series ''[[30 Rock]]''.<ref>{{cite web|work=[[NPR]]|title=How A Serious Accusation Became A Commonplace Quip|first=Neda|authorlink=Neda Ulaby|last=Ulaby|date=June 27, 2011|url=https://www.npr.org/blogs/monkeysee/2011/06/27/137451481/thats-racist-how-a-serious-accusation-became-a-commonplace-quip}}</ref> He quit after six months.<ref name=\"fishman2014\"/>\n\nHe released his second album, ''Animal Furnace'', in 2012, which also aired as a special on Comedy Central. The album received positive reviews.<ref>{{cite web|last=L. Ray|first=Austin|title=Hannibal Buress Animal Furnace DVD Review|url=http://www.thespittake.com/2012/05/18/hannibal-buress-animal-furnace-comedy-central/|publisher=The Spit Take|accessdate=April 11, 2013}}</ref>\n\nHis stand-up comedy has been featured on Comedy Central programs such as ''[[Live at Gotham]]'' and ''[[John Oliver's New York Stand-Up Show]]''. He has also performed on several late night talkshows such as ''[[The Late Late Show with Craig Ferguson]]'', ''[[Lopez Tonight]]'', ''[[Russell Howard's Good News]]'', ''[[Late Night with Jimmy Fallon]]'', ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'', ''[[Late Show with David Letterman]]'','' [[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]'', ''[[Totally Biased with W. Kamau Bell]]'', and ''[[Conan (talk show)|Conan]]''. Additionally, he performed a set at the 2012 ''[[The Secret Policeman's Balls|Secret Policeman's Ball]]'' at [[Radio City Music Hall]] in New York City.<ref>{{cite news|last=Chai|first=Barbara|title=Scenes from the Secret Policeman's Ball|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2012/03/05/scenes-from-the-secret-policemans-ball-2012/|accessdate=October 29, 2013|newspaper=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|date=March 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\nAn hourlong Comedy Central show, ''Hannibal Buress Live from Chicago'', aired on March 29, 2014.<ref name=\"fishman2014\"/>\n\nHe used to host a weekly stand-up comedy show at [[The Knitting Factory]] on Sunday evenings in [[Brooklyn, New York]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://comedyattheknittingfactory.tumblr.com/ |title=Comedy at the Knitting Factory Brooklyn with Hannibal Buress Stand Up |publisher=Comedyattheknittingfactory.tumblr.com |date= |accessdate=July 30, 2012}}</ref> In October 2016, Buress began a [[podcast]] called ''Handsome Rambler''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2016/10/20/hannibal-buresss-handsome-rambler-podcast|title=Hannibal Buress\u2019s Handsome Rambler Is The New Podcast You Need To Subscribe To|date=October 20, 2016|last=Renshaw|first=David|accessdate=April 10, 2019|work=[[The Fader]]}}</ref>\n\nBuress played Coach Wilson in the 2017 Marvel movie ''[[Spider-Man: Homecoming]]''. He paid a lookalike to attend the film's premiere in his place.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Limbachia|first1=Dixie|title=Hannibal Buress Sent an Imposter to 'Spider-Man: Homecoming\u2019 Premiere|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/hannibal-buress-sends-impersonator-spiderman-premiere-1202482849/|website=Variety|accessdate=June 30, 2017}}</ref>\n\nHe will have a comedy special for [[Cornell University]] through [[Zoom Video Communications|Zoom]] on April 17 at 9 pm exclusive to the students.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Hannibal Buress to Headline CUPB Virtual Comedy Show|url=https://cornellsun.com/2020/04/10/hannibal-buress-to-headline-cupb-virtual-comedy-show/|last=Rosenburg|first=Madeline|date=April 10, 2020|access-date=April 14, 2020|work=[[The Cornell Daily Sun]]}}</ref>\n\n=== Bill Cosby routine ===\n{{main|Bill Cosby sexual assault cases}}\nOn October 16, 2014, at the Philadelphia club [[Trocadero Theatre|The Trocadero]], Buress was recorded doing an extended routine about [[Bill Cosby sexual assault allegations|existing rape allegations against comedian Bill Cosby]].<ref name=Sarkis >{{cite web|last=Sarkis |first=Christian |url=http://www.phillymag.com/ticket/2014/09/29/photos-aziz-ansari-questions-digital-age-reads-audience-texts-wells-fargo-center-friday-night/ |title=Photos: Aziz Ansari Wells Fargo Center &#124; Ticket |publisher=Phillymag.com |date=September 29, 2014 |accessdate=October 19, 2015}}</ref> Buress addressed Cosby's legacy of \"talk[ing] down\" to young black men about their style of dress and lifestyle. Buress criticized the actor's public moralizing by saying, \"Yeah, but you raped women, Bill Cosby, so that kind of brings you down a couple notches.\" The audience appeared to respond to Buress's accusation with incredulity; he encouraged everyone to search for \"Bill Cosby rape\" on [[Google Search|Google]] when they got home.<ref name=PhillyMagBuressRoutineVideo >{{cite web| last1= McQuade| first1= Dan| title=Hannibal Buress on Bill Cosby: You're a Rapist|url=http://www.phillymag.com/ticket/2014/10/17/hannibal-buress-bill-cosby-rapist/| website= Phillymag.com| publisher= Philadelphia Magazine|accessdate=April 24, 2015|date=October 17, 2014}}</ref>\n\nBuress had been doing the same Cosby routine for the previous six months with little response,<ref name=cbs_buress>{{cite news|title=Who is Hannibal Buress, and why did he call Bill Cosby a \"rapist\"?|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/who-is-hannibal-buress-and-why-did-he-call-bill-cosby-a-rapist/|accessdate=September 30, 2015|work=CBS News|date=November 18, 2014}}</ref> but the October performance went viral after being posted on ''[[Philadelphia (magazine)|Philadelphia]]'' magazine's website.<ref name=VultureTimelineOfAccusations>{{cite web|first1= Matt |last1= Giles |first2= Nate |last2= Jones|title=A Timeline of the Abuse Charges Against Bill Cosby [Updated]|url=http://www.vulture.com/2014/09/timeline-of-the-abuse-charges-against-cosby.html| website= Vulture.com| publisher=[[New York (magazine)|New York]] |accessdate=April 24, 2015|date=March 3, 2015}}</ref><ref name=LATimesReBuressRole>{{cite news|last1=Braxton|first1=Greg|title=Comic Hannibal Buress is low-key on his role in Bill Cosby firestorm|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/la-et-st-hannibal-buress-20141124-story.html#page=1|website=Latimes.com|publisher=The Los Angeles Times|accessdate=April 24, 2015|date=November 24, 2014}}</ref> A [[media circus|media firestorm]] ensued, with numerous publications tackling the question of how Cosby had managed to maintain, as Buress called it in his set, a \"Teflon image\" despite more than a decade of public sex-abuse accusations.<ref name=nbc_cosby_why>{{cite news|title=Why Are Old Assault Claims Against Bill Cosby Back?|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/celebrity/why-are-old-assault-claims-against-bill-cosby-back-n250161|accessdate=September 30, 2015|work=CBS News|date=November 17, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"accusertable_bowman\">{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby raped me. Why did it take 30 years for people to believe my story?|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/posteverything/wp/2014/11/13/bill-cosby-raped-me-why-did-it-take-30-years-for-people-to-believe-my-story/|accessdate=September 30, 2015|work=Washington Post|date=November 13, 2014}}</ref><ref name=Evans>{{cite web|url=http://gawker.com/actress-details-years-of-alleged-rape-and-manipulation-1651808626 |title=Actress Details Years of Alleged Rape and Manipulation by Bill Cosby |author=Dayna Evans |publisher=Gawker Media |work=Gawker |accessdate=February 21, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150221052040/http://gawker.com/actress-details-years-of-alleged-rape-and-manipulation-1651808626 |archivedate=February 21, 2015 }}</ref><ref name=Bowman >{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2806437/Bill-Cosby-threw-bed-pinned-neck-ll-never-forget-sound-clinking-belt-buckle-Actress-lifts-lid-harrowing-years-rape-hands-TV-legend.html|title=Barbara Bowman reveals her years of rape at hands of Bill Cosby \u2013 Daily Mail Online|work=Mail Online|accessdate=February 21, 2015}}</ref><ref name=Shaw >{{cite web|last=Shaw |first=Maureen |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/10/22/bill-cosby-rape_n_6030242.html|title=13 Women Have Accused Bill Cosby of Rape \u2013 So Why Has America Forgiven Him?|work=The Huffington Post|accessdate=February 21, 2015}}</ref>\n\nComedian [[Eddie Murphy]] later referenced Buress's role in the allegations coming to light while impersonating Cosby during his 2015 [[Mark Twain Prize for American Humor]] acceptance speech, mockingly playing Cosby as threatening Buress' life.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/eddie-murphy-bill-cosby-impression-jokes-mark-twain-prize-1201621111/|title=Eddie Murphy Impersonates Bill Cosby While Accepting Mark Twain Prize|last=Harris|first=Paul|date=2015-10-19|work=Variety|access-date=2018-05-09|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBuress is an [[atheist]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2016/02/hannibal-buress-interview|title=Hannibal Buress Would Prefer You Didn\u2019t Snapchat a Picture of Him in Bed|last=Borden|first=Jane|work=HWD|access-date=2017-07-31|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thefader.com/2016/10/26/eric-andre-interview|title=Eric Andre Is Insanely Honest Because Who Else Is Going To Be?|website=The FADER|access-date=2017-07-31}}</ref> After living in [[New York City]], he moved back to his hometown of [[Chicago]] in 2017 and settled in its [[Wicker Park, Chicago|Wicker Park]] neighborhood.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chicago.suntimes.com/entertainment/in-baywatch-chicago-comedian-hannibal-buress-keeps-his-shirt-on/ |title=In 'Baywatch,' Chicago comedian Hannibal Buress keeps his shirt on|work=suntimes.com |date=May 22, 2017 |accessdate=June 13, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2017, Buress was arrested in [[Miami]] for [[Public intoxication|disorderly intoxication]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/biz/news/hannibal-buress-arrested-miami-disorderly-intoxication-1202635416/|title=Hannibal Buress Arrested in Miami for Disorderly Intoxication|last=Nyren|first=Erin|date=2017-12-10|work=Variety|access-date=2018-05-09|language=en-US}}</ref> Bystander footage of the arrest showed Buress mocking the police officers and demanding to know why he was being arrested.<ref name=\":0\" /> The arrest report revealed that Buress was detained because he approached the police officers and would not stop asking them to call an [[Uber]] for him.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.avclub.com/hannibal-buress-was-arrested-for-disorderly-intoxicati-1821164590|title=Hannibal Buress was apparently arrested because he kept asking a cop to call him an Uber|last=Hughes|first=William|work=The A.V. Club|access-date=2018-05-09|language=en-US}}</ref> Buress later stated, \"I asked the [officer] to call me an Uber, and he said, 'No.' He told me to leave the street. I go into this bar to get a phone charger for an Uber. He follows me into the bar, and told me I'm too drunk to go inside. [...] 'If I can't be on the street, where do you want me to be?' I ask him. I was in a state of trying to get home. [...] I don't really believe I was at fault.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.southflorida.com/theater-and-arts/sf-hannibal-buress-west-palm-beach-improv-20180123-story.html|title=Hannibal Buress on Miami arrest: 'I don\u2019t believe I was at fault'|last=Valys|first=Phillip|work=southflorida.com|access-date=2018-05-09|language=en-US}}</ref> The case was later dismissed.\n\nThe ''[[Miami New Times]]'' reported that the arresting officer has an alleged history of violence and was previously disciplined by internal affairs for an alcohol-fueled assault. This report was cited by Buress as part of a televised stand-up routine at the [[Olympia Theater (Miami)|Olympia Theater]] in Miami in August 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/crime/article233778052.html|title=Comedian Hannibal Buress rips Miami cop \u2014 and gives a shout-out to defense lawyer|last=Ovalle|first=David|work=[[Miami Herald]]|access-date=August 12, 2019|language=en-US|date=August 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.miaminewtimes.com/news/miami-cop-disciplined-for-bar-fight-after-arresting-hannibal-buress-10729875|title=Miami Cop Who Arrested Hannibal Buress Caught Choking Man After Fireball Binge|last=Iannelli|first=Jerry|work=[[Miami New Times]]|access-date=August 12, 2019|language=en-US|date=September 13, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n|2011\n|''Heart Break''\n|Darryl\n|Short film\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[Sleepwalk with Me]]''\n|Hannibal\n|Uncredited<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vulture.com/2012/08/comedians-in-sleepwalk-with-me.html|title=Meet All the Comedians in Sleepwalk With Me|website=Vulture.com|first=Eliot|last=Glazer|date=August 29, 2012|accessdate=July 6, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[The Kings of Summer]]''\n|Bus Driver\n|\n|-\n|2013\n|''Fester's Feast''\n|Milk Man\n|\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[Neighbors (2014 film)|Neighbors]]''\n|Officer Watkins\n|\n|-\n|2014\n|''The Begun of Tigtone''\n|Seed Steed (voice)\n|Short film\n|-\n|2014\n|''Are You Joking?''\n|Kenny\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Band of Robbers]]''\n|Ben Rogers\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Daddy's Home (film)|Daddy's Home]]''\n|Griff\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Nerdland]]''\n|Nerd King (voice)\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Neighbors 2: Sorority Rising]]''\n|Officer Watkins\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[The Angry Birds Movie]]''\n|Edward the Birthday Dad (voice)\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[The Nice Guys]]''\n|Bumble\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Flock of Dudes]]''\n|Pussypop\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[The Secret Life of Pets]]''\n|Buddy (voice)\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[The Comedian (2016 film)|The Comedian]]''\n|Himself\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Kuso (film)|Kuso]]''\n|Kazu\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[The Disaster Artist (film)|The Disaster Artist]]''\n|Bill Meurer\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Baywatch (film)|Baywatch]]''\n|Dave the Tech\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Spider-Man: Homecoming]]''\n|Coach Wilson\n|\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Blockers (film)|Blockers]]''\n|Frank\n| \n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Tag (2018 film)|Tag]]''\n|Kevin Sable\n|\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Slice (film)|Slice]]''\n|Hannibal\n|\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[The Secret Life of Pets 2]]''\n| Buddy (voice)\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n|2009\u20132010\n|''[[Saturday Night Live]]''\n|Michael / Airplane Passenger\n|2 episodes\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Louie (U.S. TV series)|Louie]]''\n|Hannibal\n|2 episodes\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Delocated]]''\n|Comedian #2\n|Episode: \"Kim's Krafts\"\n|-\n|2010\u20132012\n|''[[30 Rock]]''\n|Hannibal / Bum / Homeless Guy / Gus\n|9 episodes\n|-\n|2012\u2013present\n|''[[The Eric Andre Show]]''\n|Himself (co-host)\n|Also writer and producer\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[8 Out of 10 Cats]]''\n|Himself (guest / contestant)\n|Series 13, Episode 2 (4 May 2012)\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[The Mindy Project]]''\n|Derek\n|Episode: \"Bunk Bed\"\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[Kroll Show]]''\n|Basketball Player\n|Episode: \"Dine & Dash\"\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[High Maintenance (TV series)|High Maintenance Web Series]]''\n|Hannibal\n|Episode: \"Jonathan\"\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[Bob's Burgers]]''\n|Hefty Jeff (voice)\n|Episode: \"My Big Fat Greek Bob\"\n|-\n|2013\u20132015\n|''[[Lucas Bros. Moving Co.]]''\n|Momma Lucas (Voice)\n|7 episodes\n|-\n|2013\u20132015\n|''[[China, IL]]''\n|Matt Attack / DJ Don Jose / Street Troll (voice)\n|9 episodes\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[Chozen]]''\n|Crisco (voice)\n|10 episodes\n|-\n|2014\u20132019\n|''[[Broad City]]''\n|Lincoln Rice\n|20 episodes\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[The Comedy Central Roast of Justin Bieber]]''\n|Himself\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Why? with Hannibal Buress]]''\n|Himself (host)\n|Also creator and executive producer\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[The Jim Gaffigan Show]]''\n|Himself\n|Episode: \"Maria\"\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Childrens Hospital]]''\n|Himself\n|Episode: \"Kids Hospital\"\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Adventure Time]]''\n|Flame Prince (voice)\n|Episode: \"Five Short Tables\"\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Easy (TV series)|Easy]]''\n|Jason\n|Episode: \"Hop Dreams\"\n|-\n|2016\u20132017\n|''[[High Maintenance]]''\n|Comedian\n|2 e